<% content_for :title, "COVID-19 Instructions — AACT" %>

<div class="max-w-5xl pl-12 space-y-10">
  <div class="mb-8">
    <%= render "shared/back_link", path: snapshots_path, label: "Snapshots" %>
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-2">COVID-19 Spreadsheet Instructions</h1>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-lg p-4">
    <p class="text-sm text-yellow-800">
      <strong>Please Note:</strong> COVID-19 spreadsheets are no longer actively generated. Please check
      the "Last Exported" date on the snapshots page for the most recent available data.
    </p>
  </div>

  <section>
    <h2 class="relative block w-full pl-4 text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4 pb-2 border-b border-gray-200 before:content-[''] before:absolute before:left-0 before:top-0 before:w-1.5 before:h-6 before:bg-navy before:rounded-sm">Overview</h2>
    <div class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-3">
      <p>
        The following files contain clinical studies related to <strong>Coronavirus Disease 2019
        (COVID-19)</strong> from ClinicalTrials.gov as of the date and time of file creation. There may
        be more studies on ClinicalTrials.gov that were uploaded after the most recent file here. Each
        file allows users without advanced database skills to explore the trials in a spreadsheet format.
      </p>
      <p>
        The spreadsheet was created using
        <a href="https://clinicaltrials.gov/search?cond=COVID-19" class="text-blue hover:underline" target="_blank">ClinicalTrials.gov's COVID-19 search criteria</a>
        and the database for Aggregate Analysis of ClinicalTrials.gov (AACT). This search strategy
        includes specific terms and filters to identify all COVID-19 related trials.
      </p>
      <p>
        Each study appears as a single row in the spreadsheet with 68 columns of study information,
        including study identifiers, titles, conditions, interventions, locations, and results status.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 class="relative block w-full pl-4 text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4 pb-2 border-b border-gray-200 before:content-[''] before:absolute before:left-0 before:top-0 before:w-1.5 before:h-6 before:bg-navy before:rounded-sm">Steps</h2>
    <ol class="space-y-6">
      <li class="flex gap-4">
        <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-navy text-white text-sm font-bold rounded-full flex items-center justify-center">1</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-medium text-gray-900 mb-1">Download a COVID-19 spreadsheet</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
            View and download available COVID-19 spreadsheets from the
            <%= link_to "COVID-19 archive", archive_snapshots_path(type: "covid"), class: "text-blue hover:underline" %> page.
            These files contain historical data from when COVID-19 spreadsheets were still being generated.
            For the most current clinical trial information, please visit
            <a href="https://clinicaltrials.gov/search?cond=COVID-19" class="text-blue hover:underline" target="_blank">ClinicalTrials.gov</a> directly.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>

      <li class="flex gap-4">
        <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-navy text-white text-sm font-bold rounded-full flex items-center justify-center">2</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-medium text-gray-900 mb-1">Open with spreadsheet software</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
            Open the downloaded file in <strong>Microsoft Excel, Google Sheets, or LibreOffice Calc</strong>.
            Each row represents a single clinical trial, with columns containing various attributes of the study.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </section>

</div>
